{"type":"text","timestamp":1775838798063,"sessionID":"ses_287c2f75bffeONNHrZmNLUqXch","part":{"id":"prt_d783d9e88001BLBRkxRLzEb4Hh","messageID":"msg_d783d8ffd0013KeEunNb1EAgWq","sessionID":"ses_287c2f75bffeONNHrZmNLUqXch","type":"text","text":"Now I have enough context to write the proposal.md. Based on the task requirements and the information gathered, I'll create a comprehensive proposal for AR-001:","time":{"start":1775838798061,"end":1775838798061}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775838830567,"sessionID":"ses_287c2f75bffeONNHrZmNLUqXch","part":{"id":"prt_d783da0ef001iRKFqNwS0grSxa","messageID":"msg_d783d8ffd0013KeEunNb1EAgWq","sessionID":"ses_287c2f75bffeONNHrZmNLUqXch","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_79a23a0535fd43f2b9837373","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md","content":"# Proposal: AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) and associated types for the AgentCube platform. This CRD enables users to declare and manage AI agent runtime configurations as Kubernetes-native resources, providing the foundation for sandbox orchestration and lifecycle management.\n\nThe `AgentRuntime` resource represents a configurable agent execution environment with support for:\n- Code interpreter attachment\n- Resource quotas (CPU, memory, storage)\n- Network policies and egress rules\n- Lifecycle hooks (preStart, postStop)\n- Status tracking (phase, conditions, sandbox reference)\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**API Group:** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`  \n**Kind:** `AgentRuntime` (namespaced)  \n**Size:** S\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **Type Definitions** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`)\n   - `AgentRuntime` - main resource struct\n   - `AgentRuntimeSpec` - desired state specification\n   - `AgentRuntimeStatus` - observed state status\n   - `CodeInterpreterSpec` - embedded code interpreter configuration\n   - `ResourceQuota` - sandbox resource limits\n   - `NetworkPolicy` - egress/ingress rules\n   - `LifecycleHook` - preStart/postStop callbacks\n   - `AgentRuntimePhase` - lifecycle phase enum\n   - `AgentRuntimeCondition` - status conditions\n\n2. **API Registration** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go`)\n   - `SchemeGroupVersion` definition\n   - `SchemeBuilder` registration\n   - `AddToScheme` function\n   - `Resource` and `Kind` helpers\n\n3. **CRD Manifest** (`manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml`)\n   - OpenAPI v3 schema validation\n   - Subresources: `/status`, `/scale` (if needed)\n   - AdditionalPrinterColumns for kubectl output\n   - Conversion webhook placeholders (future)\n\n4. **Defaulting & Validation** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/defaults.go`, `validation.go`)\n   - `SetDefaults_AgentRuntime` - default values\n   - `ValidateAgentRuntime` - spec validation rules\n   - `ValidateAgentRuntimeStatusUpdate` - status update validation\n\n5. **Utility Functions**\n   - Phase transition helpers\n   - Condition management (GetCondition, SetCondition, RemoveCondition)\n   - Deep copy utilities (via code generation)\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Controller implementation (covered by AR-002)\n- Webhook admission controllers (deferred to AR-010)\n- Conversion webhooks for version upgrades (deferred)\n- CLI commands for AgentRuntime (Python SDK task)\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Type | Reason |\n|------------|------|--------|\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Required | MetaV1 types, runtime.Object, schema |\n| `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Required | ResourceList, PodSecurityContext, EnvVar |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | Generated | Clientset, listers, informers (via `make gen-client`) |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis` | Module | API group registration |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **Controller (AR-002)**: Watches `AgentRuntime` resources, reconciles to create sandbox pods\n2. **Router**: Reads `AgentRuntime` status to route traffic to active sandboxes\n3. **Python SDK**: Provides high-level API for creating/managing AgentRuntime resources\n4. **CLI Tool**: Exposes `agentcube runtime create/get/list/delete` commands\n5. **Helm Chart**: Ships CRD manifest for cluster installation\n\n### Breaking Changes\n\nNone - this is the initial definition of the API.\n\n### Migration Path\n\nNot applicable for initial implementation. Future version migrations (v1alpha2, v1beta1) will require:\n- Conversion webhook implementation\n- Storage version bumps\n- helm chart upgrade hooks\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Use Deployment + ConfigMap instead of CRD\n\n**Approach:** Represent agent runtimes as standard Kubernetes Deployments with configuration in ConfigMaps.\n\n**Pros:**\n- No CRD complexity or controller required\n- Leverages built-in Kubernetes primitives\n- Simpler RBAC story\n\n**Cons:**\n- Loses semantic meaning (Deployment is generic)\n- Complex validation logic in admission webhooks\n- Status reporting requires custom annotations\n- Harder to query/filter agent-specific resources\n- No custom subresources (e.g., `/exec`, `/logs` future extensions)\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. CRD provides better abstraction, type safety, and extensibility for AgentCube semantics.\n\n### Alternative 2: Single monolithic AgentRuntime CRD with all features\n\n**Approach:** Include all possible configuration options (networking, storage, auth, scheduling) in one large spec.\n\n**Pros:**\n- One resource to rule them all\n- Maximum flexibility for users\n\n**Cons:**\n- High cognitive load for simple use cases\n- Validation complexity\n- Harder to evolve individual aspects\n- Violates separation of concerns\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. Prefer composable design with `CodeInterpreter` as separate but related resource. Core `AgentRuntime` focuses on execution environment; advanced features (distributed training, multi-agent orchestration) can be future extensions.\n\n### Alternative 3: Use Pod-level primitives (PodTemplate) directly\n\n**Approach:** Embed raw PodTemplateSpec in AgentRuntime spec.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Full Kubernetes pod configuration available\n- No translation layer needed\n\n**Cons:**\n- Exposes low-level K8s details to end users\n- Harder to enforce platform policies\n- Breaks abstraction if K8s pod spec changes\n\n**Decision:** Partially adopted. AgentRuntimeSpec contains a simplified `Container` subset (image, env, resources) rather than full PodSpec, with controller translating to Pod internals. This balances flexibility with abstraction.\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n1. **Scaffold directory structure**\n   - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n   - `pkg/apis/runtime/register.go` (group registration)\n\n2. **Define Go types** (`types.go`)\n   - Core structs with JSON tags\n   - Phase enum and conditions\n   - Embedded CodeInterpreterSpec\n\n3. **Implement registration** (`register.go`)\n   - SchemeGroupVersion constants\n   - SchemeBuilder wiring\n\n4. **Add defaults and validation**\n   - `defaults.go`: SetDefaults_AgentRuntime\n   - `validation.go`: ValidateAgentRuntime\n\n5. **Generate CRD manifest**\n   - Run `make gen-crd` (controller-gen)\n   - Place in `manifests/charts/base/crds/`\n\n6. **Generate client code**\n   - Run `make gen-client` (code-generator)\n   - Produces clientset, listers, informers\n\n7. **Write unit tests**\n   - Type round-trip serialization\n   - Defaulting behavior\n   - Validation rules\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] `AgentRuntime` CRD installs via Helm chart\n- [ ] `kubectl apply -f agentruntime.yaml` succeeds\n- [ ] `kubectl get agentruntime` shows custom columns\n- [ ] Go client can create/get/update AgentRuntime\n- [ ] Spec validation rejects invalid resources\n- [ ] Defaulting applies expected values\n- [ ] Code generation produces compilable client-go code\n\n## References\n\n- [Kubernetes API Conventions](https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md)\n- [Controller Tools CRD Generation](https://book.kubebuilder.io/reference/markers/crd.html)\n- [Kubernetes Code Generator](https://github.com/kubernetes/code-generator)\n- AgentCube deployment spec: `deployment/spec.md`\n- Client-go reference: `deployment/client-go.md`\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775838830556,"end":1775838830564}}}}
